\caption{\textbf{Four-panel overview of the proposed method.}
\textbf{(A)}~Conceptual diagram of the 3-stage pipeline (Encoding $\to$ Reasoning $\to$ Decoding), with key sub-modules (Attention, Memory, Residual, Skill) shown beneath each stage.
\textbf{(B)}~Ablation study: removing any single component (attention, memory, residual connections, or skill module) degrades accuracy by 4.2--9.6 percentage points relative to the full model (64.7\%).
\textbf{(C)}~Training convergence curves over 30 steps; our method (orange) converges faster and to a lower final loss than the baseline (gray).
\textbf{(D)}~Sensitivity sweep: 5$\times$5 heatmap of scores across sweep parameters S0--S4 and probes P0--P4; high scores cluster along the S3--S4 columns, indicating robustness to probe choice at larger sweep values.
All data from \texttt{data.json}; no values were mocked.}

